When would you want to use a remote repository rather than keeping all your work
local?

    It could get lost or other people could contribute to the project remotely
    
Why might you want to always pull changes manually rather than having Git
automatically stay up-to-date with your remote repository?

    Because you don't want code changes to be happening without you being aware - it would be very confusing to trace down bugs

Describe the differences between forks, clones, and branches.  When would you
use one instead of another?

    Forks are used primarily to clone GitHub repos so another user can make changes - this is different from normal cloning which is done 
    on the local machine or from GitHub to your local machine - branches are new versions of code "branched" off from a current stream of commits
